definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
Italy/Italian/abbr. for 意大利[Yi4 da4 li4]
Italy/Italian/abbr. for 意大利[Yi4 da4 li4]

sentences.english: All of us apply this method knowingly or unknowingly.
sentences.chinese: 其實我們有意無意的都在使用這種方法。

sentences.english: Intentionally or not, it seems customers are being mislead.
sentences.chinese: 有意無意地，似乎消費者們被誤導了。

sentences.english: By coincidence or design, they are moderated extrapolations of current trends.
sentences.chinese: 有意無意地，這些預測是對目前勢態的保守推演。

sentences.english: The visualization problem was normally ignored in the past terminology research.
sentences.chinese: 形象性問題在以往的術語研究中被有意無意地迴避。

sentences.english: Unwittingly, Cournot had stumbled across an example of a Nash equilibrium.
sentences.chinese: 有意無意之間，古諾發現了一個納什均衡的例子。
